25|$|During {{the late}} 1950s, California was {{a focus for}} Halloween haunts. In 1957, the San Mateo <b>Haunted</b> <b>House</b> opened, {{sponsored}} by the Children’s Health Home Junior Auxiliary. The San Bernardino Assistance League <b>Haunted</b> <b>House</b> opened in 1958. In 1962 and 1963 home haunts began appearing across the country, including Oregon, California, Connecticut, Illinois and several other states. On October 17th, 1964, the San Manteo <b>Haunted</b> <b>House</b> opened as a walk-through <b>haunted</b> <b>house.</b> The Children’s Museum <b>Haunted</b> <b>House</b> in Indianapolis, open every year since 1964, was Indiana’s first <b>haunted</b> <b>house</b> and is currently the longest running in the nation.|$|E
